{"parse":{"title":"Geographical Range","pageid":435,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The greatest distance at which an object or a light source can be seen under conditions of perfect visibility, as limited only by the curvature of the earth, by refraction of the atmosphere, and by the elevation of the observer and the object or light.\n</p><p><span class=\"mw-image-border\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:Ch2_Fig9.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/9/9d/Ch2_Fig9.jpg/400px-Ch2_Fig9.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"400\" height=\"143\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/9/9d/Ch2_Fig9.jpg/600px-Ch2_Fig9.jpg 1.5x, /wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/9/9d/Ch2_Fig9.jpg/800px-Ch2_Fig9.jpg 2x\" /></a></span>\n</p><p><br />\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\" /></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/Codes_on_Alerts_and_Indicators\" title=\"Codes on Alerts and Indicators\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260616011756\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.034 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.042 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 58/1000000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 733/2